This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as opinion words extraction and sentiment analysis. Additionally, the use of neural network methods in this paper further supports this categorization. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel model that utilizes transfer learning techniques to improve the performance of a low-resource task. 

Furthermore, the paper may fall under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the extraction of opinions and sentiments from text, which is a common task in AI research. 

The sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possibility as the paper deals with the extraction of opinion words from text, which is a common task in information retrieval. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper deals with sentiment analysis and opinion extraction, which are important tasks in social media analysis and network analysis.
